<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900">

<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8"/>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
    <meta name="color-scheme" content="light dark"/>
    <meta name="robots" content="noindex, nofollow, noarchive, nosnippet"/>
    <base href="/"/>
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/favicon.png"/>

    @* AppBlueprint UiKit (Tailwind + Cruip design system) *@
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/AppBlueprint.UiKit/css/app.css"/>

    @* Z.Blazor.Diagrams *@
    <link href="/_content/Z.Blazor.Diagrams/style.min.css" rel="stylesheet"/>
    <link href="/_content/Z.Blazor.Diagrams/default.styles.min.css" rel="stylesheet"/>

    @* The Cruip sidebar template locks the sidebar open at the 2xl breakpoint
       (>=1536px), which made the desktop collapse toggle appear to do nothing on
       wide monitors. The shared UiKit menu components keep their labels/chevron
       visible via 2xl: utilities; neutralize those locks when the sidebar is
       collapsed so the toggle governs the rail at all desktop widths. *@
    <style>
        @@media (min-width: 1536px) {
            body:not(.sidebar-expanded) #sidebar .\32 xl\:opacity-100 { opacity: 0 !important; }
            body:not(.sidebar-expanded) #sidebar .\32 xl\:block { display: none !important; }
        }

        /* Per-app branding. MainLayout sets --brand-* on the app content container; these read
           them and fall back to the shell's default violet (violet-500/600) when unbranded. */
        .btn-brand {
            display: inline-flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 0.5rem;
            padding: 0.5rem 0.875rem;
            font-size: 0.875rem;
            font-weight: 500;
            color: var(--brand-on-primary, #ffffff);
            background-color: var(--brand-primary, #8b5cf6);
            border-radius: var(--brand-radius, 0.375rem);
            border: 1px solid transparent;
            box-shadow: 0 1px 2px 0 rgb(0 0 0 / 0.05);
            transition: background-color 0.15s ease-in-out, box-shadow 0.15s ease-in-out;
        }
        .btn-brand:hover { background-color: var(--brand-primary-hover, #7c3aed); }
        /* In dark mode boost the button so it reads clearly on dark backgrounds */
        @@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
            .btn-brand {
                box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px rgb(255 255 255 / 0.1), 0 1px 2px 0 rgb(0 0 0 / 0.4);
            }
        }
        :is(.dark .btn-brand) {
            box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px rgb(255 255 255 / 0.1), 0 1px 2px 0 rgb(0 0 0 / 0.4);
        }
        .brand-tab-active {
            color: var(--brand-primary, #8b5cf6) !important;
            border-color: var(--brand-primary, #8b5cf6) !important;
        }
    </style>

    <HeadOutlet/>
</head>

<body class="font-inter antialiased bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 sidebar-expanded">
<script src="/js/app-init.js"></script>
<Routes @rendermode="InteractiveServer"/>

@* AppBlueprint UiKit sidebar/theme JS *@
<script src="/AppBlueprint.UiKit/js/site.js"></script>

@* Z.Blazor.Diagrams *@
<script src="/_content/Z.Blazor.Diagrams/script.min.js"></script>

<script src="/_framework/blazor.web.js"></script>
</body>

</html>
